            <div class="section">
                <h2>Combat Rotation</h2>
                <p>The rotation revolves around leveraging your three golems for consistent damage while building up to Army of the Dead burst windows. Group enemies with Corpse Tendrils, then chain Corpse Explosions during high-density moments.</p>

                <ol class="rotation-steps">
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <div>
                            <p><strong style="color: #d4af37;">Summon All Three Golems</strong></p>
                            <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.85rem;">At the start of combat or when golems die, cast Golem to summon all three variants (Bone, Blood, Iron). With Gravebloom Maze, this single cast brings out your entire golem army. Your golems are your primary damage dealers -- keep them alive and active at all times.</p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <div>
                            <p><strong style="color: #d4af37;">Corpse Tendrils to Pull + Vulnerable</strong></p>
                            <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.85rem;">Use Corpse Tendrils to pull all nearby enemies into a tight group and stun them. This applies Vulnerable and ensures your golems and Corpse Explosions hit maximum targets. Positioning is key -- pull enemies into your golem cluster for maximum damage overlap.</p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <div>
                            <p><strong style="color: #d4af37;">Let Golems Generate Corpses</strong></p>
                            <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.85rem;">Your three golems kill enemies constantly, generating corpses naturally. Wait for 2-3 corpses to accumulate before starting your Corpse Explosion chain. Use Reap to supplement corpse generation if needed, but prioritize letting golems do the work.</p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <div>
                            <p><strong style="color: #d4af37;">Chain Corpse Explosions</strong></p>
                            <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.85rem;">With enemies grouped and multiple corpses available, spam Corpse Explosion. Each explosion deals massive AoE damage, generates more corpses from kills, and chains into the next explosion. In dense packs, explosions create a feedback loop of corpse generation and burst damage.</p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <div>
                            <p><strong style="color: #d4af37;">Army of the Dead During Density</strong></p>
                            <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.85rem;">Save Army of the Dead for high-density windows. After pulling enemies with Corpse Tendrils and with your golems attacking, cast Army of the Dead for a massive burst. Supreme Army extends the duration per kill, so the more enemies you hit, the longer the ultimate lasts.</p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <div>
                            <p><strong style="color: #d4af37;">Decrepify -- Auto-Applied</strong></p>
                            <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.85rem;">With Aspect of the Cursed Aura, Decrepify automatically applies to all nearby enemies. You do not need to cast it manually. Enemies are constantly slowed, deal reduced damage, and trigger Abhorrent Decrepify CDR when they die, reducing your Army of the Dead cooldown.</p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <div>
                            <p><strong style="color: #d4af37;">Reap for Buffs</strong></p>
                            <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.85rem;">Use Reap every 3-4 seconds to maintain Acolyte's Reap damage reduction and attack speed buffs. This also generates additional corpses when golem kills are slow. One swing is enough -- do not spam.</p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>Tips & Advanced Play</h2>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Golem AI Management</strong>
                    <p>Your golems follow you and attack nearby enemies, but their AI can be unreliable. Position yourself near high-priority targets to direct golem attacks. If golems are stuck or attacking the wrong target, move closer to the enemy you want them to focus.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Corpse Economy Balance</strong>
                    <p>Do not blow every corpse on Corpse Explosion -- always save 1-2 corpses for Corpse Tendrils CC. Without Corpse Tendrils, you lose your grouping tool and Vulnerable application, which cripples your burst damage.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Army of the Dead Timing</strong>
                    <p>Army of the Dead has a long cooldown. Use it only during high-density pulls or boss burn phases. Cast it after Corpse Tendrils groups enemies, and aim the cone to hit as many targets as possible. Each kill extends the duration via Supreme Army, so hitting more enemies = longer ultimate uptime.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Boss Strategy</strong>
                    <p>Against bosses, let your three golems tank and deal consistent damage. Use Corpse Tendrils to root the boss in place. Save Army of the Dead for when the boss summons adds or reaches a damage window. Corpse Explosion is less effective on single-target, so focus on maintaining golem uptime and Reap buffs.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Kalan's Edict Uptime</strong>
                    <p>With your minions tanking, Kalan's Edict barrier should have high uptime. If the barrier breaks, reposition behind your golems for 3 seconds to let it refresh. Do not face-tank damage -- let your minions do the work.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Deathspeaker's Pendant Synergy</strong>
                    <p>Deathspeaker's Pendant triggers Blood Surge from your minions on every kill. Position yourself near your golems so the Blood Surge casts hit enemies in range, providing additional damage and healing. This sustain is critical for maintaining Kalan's Edict barrier uptime.</p>
                </div>
